# ─── DATABASE ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# WHAT: The SQLite database files (created automatically by db.py and
#       booking.py's save_booking_audit()).
# WHY: Never commit these to Git — leads.db holds lead PII (names,
#      emails, phone numbers, budgets) and bookings.db holds the same
#      for every confirmed booking (bookings_audit table: email, name,
#      need). Both will differ on every machine/deployment. bookings.db
#      was previously missing from this file — if you've already
#      committed it, run a history-rewrite (e.g. `git filter-repo` or
#      the BFG Repo-Cleaner) to remove it from past commits too, since
#      gitignore only stops FUTURE commits.
leads.db
leads.db-journal
bookings.db
bookings.db-journal

# ─── ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES ───────────────────────────────────────────
# WHAT: Your .env file with API keys and secrets.
# WHY: Never commit API keys, webhook URLs, or other secrets to Git.
.env
.env.local
.env.*.local

# ─── PYTHON COMPILED FILES ───────────────────────────────────────────
# WHAT: Python bytecode cache files.
# WHY: These are auto-generated and not needed in version control.
__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.pyo
*.pyd
*.pyc

# ─── PYTHON DISTRIBUTION / BUILD ─────────────────────────────────────
# WHAT: Build artifacts when packaging the project.
# WHY: These are generated, not source code.
build/
dist/
*.egg-info/
*.egg
.eggs/

# ─── VIRTUAL ENVIRONMENTS ────────────────────────────────────────────
# WHAT: Python virtual environment folders.
# WHY: These are large, machine-specific, and not needed in Git.
venv/
env/
.venv/
ENV/
env.bak/
venv.bak/

# ─── IDE CONFIGURATION ───────────────────────────────────────────────
# WHAT: IDE-specific settings and project files.
# WHY: These are personal preference and should not be shared.
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp
*.swo
*~
.DS_Store
.project
.classpath
.settings/

# ─── TESTING / COVERAGE ──────────────────────────────────────────────
# WHAT: Test artifacts and coverage reports.
# WHY: These are generated during testing, not source code.
.pytest_cache/
.coverage
htmlcov/
.tox/
.mypy_cache/
.ruff_cache/

# ─── LOGS ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# WHAT: Application log files.
# WHY: Logs are generated at runtime and contain machine-specific data.
*.log
logs/

# ─── TEMPORARY FILES ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
# WHAT: OS and editor temporary files.
# WHY: These are not part of the project.
*.tmp
*.temp
*.bak
*.backup

# ─── DEPLOYMENT ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# WHAT: Deployment-specific files (Railway, Heroku, etc.)
# WHY: These are generated during deployment, not part of source code.
railway.json
.railway/

# ─── SECURITY ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# WHAT: Security-sensitive files.
# WHY: Never commit private keys or credential files.
*.key
*.pem
*.crt
*.p12

# ─── MISC ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# WHAT: OS-specific junk files.
# WHY: Not part of the project.
Thumbs.db
desktop.ini
.DS_Store